title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_01
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Bowl: A curved stroke enclosing the counterform of a letter.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_02
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Ear: A small stroke that projects from the upper right side of the bowl of the lowercase roman g.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_03
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Link: The stroke that connects the bowl and the loop of a lowercase roman g.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_04
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Descender: A stroke on a lowercase letterform that falls below the baseline.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_05
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Loop: The bottom form of the lowercase roman g.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_06
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Apex: The peak of the triangle of an uppercase A.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_07
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Hairline: The thinnest stroke within a typeface that has strokes of varying weights.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_08
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Fillet: The contoured edge that connects the serif and stem in bracketed serifs.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_09
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Crossbar: The horizontal stroke connecting two sides of the letterform (as in e, A, and H) or bisecting the main stroke (as in f and t).

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_10
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Arm: A projecting horizontal stroke that is unattached on one or both ends, as in the letters T and E.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_11
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Stem: A major vertical or diagonal stroke in the letterform.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_12
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Terminal: The end of any stroke that does not terminate with a serif.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_13
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Ascender: A stroke on a lowercase letter that rises above the meanline.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_14
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Leg: The lower diagonal stroke on the letter k.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_15
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Shoulder: A curved stroke projecting from a stem.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_16
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Stroke: Any of the linear elements within a letterform; originally, any mark or dash made by the movement of a pen or brush in writing.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_17
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Tail: A diagonal stroke or loop at the end of a letter, as in R or j.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_18
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Serif: Short stroke that extends from and at an angle to the upper and lower ends of the major strokes of a letterform.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_19
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Counter: The negative space that is fully or partially enclosed by a letterform.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_20
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Spur: A projection smaller than a serif that reinforces the point at the end of a curved stroke, as in the letter G.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_21
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Spine: The central curved stroke of the letter S.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_22
frontText: Name the part of the letterform identified by the arrow
backText: Eye: The enclosed part of the lowercase e.

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_23
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Garamond: Classification: Old Style

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_24
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Garamond: Classification: Italic

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_25
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Baskerville: Classification: Transitional

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_26
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Bodoni: Classification: Modern

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_27
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Serifa: Classification: Egyptian

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_28
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Franklin Gothic: Classification: Sans Serif, Grotesque

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_29
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Helvetica: Classification: Sans Serif, Neo-Grotesque

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_30
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Meta: Classification: Sans Serif, Humanist

title: 312567_TypoDes7E_FC_31
frontText: Name the typeface and its historical classification
backText: Futura: Classification: Sans Serif, Geometric
